      "id": "sab_scene",
      "title": "The Sabotage",
      "text": "Cargo hold. Torn grain spills like sand. Four sailors line up by lanternlight. Istra: 'One lie, three truths.'\\n\\nHarl (rope-burned): 'I was above deck when it happened.'\\nBranik (narrow eyes): 'I saw Harl in the hold just before the grain was found ruined.'\\nOdran (steady): 'I was fixing ropes in the hold the whole time.'\\nTorvald (neutral): 'I saw Odran working on the ropes, true. But I never saw Harl anywhere near the deck.'\\n\\nOnly one statement is a lie.",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": "inspect_scene",
